## Digital Currents

A constant **tapping** on the glass takes hold,
The screen's bright lure commands the waking hour,
A stream of pixels, stories bought and sold,
Exerts a soft, yet strangely **compelling** power.
This digital domain, a boundless sea,
Where fleeting fame becomes the traded good,
Demands attention paid perpetually,
As measured by the clicks misunderstood.
Our focus is the **currency** they crave,
The coin exchanged for shallow, quick delight,
While deeper currents whisper, strong and brave,
Beyond the glow of artificial light.
